  <div class="container">
    <h1>Climate Services Dashboard</h1>
    <p>
      The Climate Hazards Center (CHC) supports climate services that strengthen decision-making and resilience across the globe. 
      Below are three key components of CHC’s climate service initiatives.
    </p>

    <!-- Section 1: Early Warning -->
<div class="section">
  <h2>
    <a href="https://snippets.chc.ucsb.edu/climateservices/earlywarning.html">Early Warning</a>
  </h2>
  <p>
    The CHC advances early warning systems for droughts, floods, and heat hazards by integrating satellite data, 
    ground observations, and model-based forecasts. Through partnerships with various organizations the CHC supports the monitoring and forecasting of 
    extreme climate events.
  </p>
</div>

  <!-- Section 2: Capacity Building -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Capacity Building</h2>
    <p>
      CHC works with global and regional partners through training programs and collaborative workshops to strengthen 
      climate monitoring and forecasting capabilities. These initiatives help National Meteorological and Hydrological Centers 
      improve their ability to interpret, communicate, and act on climate information.
    </p>
     </div>

  <!-- Section 3: Snippets -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Snippets</h2>
    <p>
      Snippets are interactive web tools that let users embed near real-time climate maps from the
      <a href="https://chc.ucsb.edu/tools/ewx">Early Warning eXplorer (EWX)</a> directly into their own websites. 
      These tools allow National Meteorological and Hydrological Services and humanitarian partners 
      to display CHC’s climate visualizations locally, improving access to actionable early warning information.
    </p>
    <p>
      Learn more: <a href="https://chc.ucsb.edu/data/snippets">Visit the CHC Snippets Page</a>
    </p>
